    <stitle>9 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT-8609 SERIES - REMOVE - LEFT REVERSE IDLER GEAR ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="6">
        <title>LEFT REVERSE IDLER GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302969">Figure 69</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1302969" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302969" filename="../figg13/g1302969.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 69. Left Reverse Idler Gear Assembly Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use inside jaw pullers or impact puller to remove the auxiliary countershaft front bearing
                from the left reverse idler gear bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302970">Figure 70</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302970" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302970" filename="../figg13/g1302970.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 70. Remove Auxiliary Countershaft Front Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the idler shaft plug from the rear of the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302971">Figure 71</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302971" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302971" filename="../figg13/g1302971.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 71. Remove Idler Shaft Plug</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With a 15/16 inch socket, remove the stop nut from the front of the idler shaft and remove
                the washer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302972">Figure 72</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302972" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302972" filename="../figg13/g1302972.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 72. Remove Stop Nut From Front of Idler Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use an impact puller, 1/2"-13 threaded end, to remove the idler shaft from the case bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302973">Figure 73</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302973" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302973" filename="../figg13/g1302973.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 73. Remove Idler Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">As the idler shaft is moved to the rear, remove the thrust washer and gear from the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302974">Figure 74</hotlnk>). If necessary, remove the bearing from the bore of the
                reverse idler gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302974">inset</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302974" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302974" filename="../figg13/g1302974.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 74. Remove Thrust Washer and Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
